cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper proposes a method to improve image labeling by extracting visual features from synthetic images generated by a modified version of a Text-to-image GAN. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing and text interpretation, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of adversarial learning also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval and feature extraction, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
